        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "$bbcode = Zend_Markup::factory('Bbcode', 'Html', array('useDefaultFilters' => false));\r\nhas no effect.  render() method in RendererAbstract calls getDefaultFilter() which in turn calls addDefaultFilters() without checking for the option.  It does not even have a way to check for that option because __constructor() keeps the options in local scope.\r\nI suggest adding a protected property $_options and assign to it the $options array in construct so that addDefaultFilters() method can check for its value with \r\n\r\nif (null === $this->_defaultFilter && (!isset($this->_options['useDefaultFilters']) || ($this->_options['useDefaultFilters'] === true)) ) {"
        },
